E-Commerce Backend Project
Overview
This project is a backend implementation of an e-commerce shopping application using JavaEE. It provides functionalities for user authentication,
product management, and order processing. The application is built using JSP, Servlets, and MySQL for data storage. JWT is used for authorization,
ensuring secure access to the system.

Features
    User Authentication: Sign in and Sign up functionalities with JWT for secure authorization.
    Product Management: Adding, updating, and removing products from the catalog.
    Cart Management: Adding items to the cart, updating item quantities, and removing items.
    Order Management: Placing orders, canceling orders, and checking out.
Technologies Used
    JavaEE: Core framework for building the application.
    JSP and Servlets: For handling HTTP requests and responses.
    MySQL: Database for storing user, product, and order information.
    JWT: For secure authorization.
    HTML, CSS, JS: For creating the user interface.
Project Structure
Model Classes
    Cart: Represents a shopping cart.
    Order: Represents an order placed by a user.
    Product: Represents a product available in the store.
    User: Represents a user in the system.
Data Access Object (DAO) Layer
    OrderDao: Handles database operations related to orders.
    ProductDao: Handles database operations related to products.
    UserDao: Handles database operations related to users.
Servlets
    AddToCartServlet: Adds a product to the shopping cart.
    CancelOrderServlet: Cancels an existing order.
    CheckoutServlet: Handles the checkout process.
    OrderNowServlet: Places an order directly.
    QuantityIncDecServlet: Increases or decreases the quantity of an item in the cart.
    RemoveFromCartServlet: Removes an item from the cart.
User Interface
    HTML/CSS/JS: Provides the front-end for user interactions.
Setup Instructions
Prerequisites
    Java Development Kit (JDK) 8 or higher
    Apache Tomcat or any other compatible servlet container
    MySQL Database
Installation
Clone the repository
    sh
    Copy code
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/ecommerce-backend.git
    cd ecommerce-backend
Set up the database

Create a new MySQL database.
Run the provided SQL scripts to create the necessary tables.
Configure the application

Update the database connection details in the project configuration files.
Deploy to a servlet container

Package the application as a WAR file and deploy it to your servlet container (e.g., Apache Tomcat).
Run the application

Start your servlet container and access the application through your browser.
Usage
    Sign Up: Create a new user account.
    Sign In: Log in with your credentials.
    Browse Products: View the list of available products.
    Add to Cart: Add desired products to your shopping cart.
    Update Cart: Increase or decrease the quantity of items in your cart.
    Remove from Cart: Remove items from your cart.
    Checkout: Proceed to checkout and place your order.
    Order Now: Directly place an order for a product.
    Cancel Order: Cancel an order that you have placed.
